µC0For which system do you plan to code in the future - classic Amigas, PPC or for the Amiga One?

µC2I will support karate68k when needed, but I am currently working on AmigaOS4... and PC in fact. I like the scene we have today, on PC and Amiga. Really. When I see a MFX or Kewlers demo, I'm just too happy: the scene had evolved just the way I wanted it to evolve, It is incredibly interesting to participate to all this.



µC0I saw at the Breakpoint that you own an Amiga One on your own. Maybe you want to share your experiences with this piece of hardware with us.

µC2Actually I own a pegasos+morphos since 2 years, and an AmigaOne+os4 since two months. How crazy I am, I paid for the both. I swear I will not buy Amiga hardware for years now. They have a lot of common points, but they have differents kernels.

µC2AmigaOS4 was late until recently, now they are more or less at the same points in term of functionnalities. There are some GCC SDK for each, it is very very handy. It allows to rebuild amiga68k applications to native PowerPC ones. But the big question is: how will the systems evolve, in term of memory protections and all that stuffs. Actually, the technical aspect is not so that important when you compare the both, not only because they look the same, but because evolutions are mainly a matter of time and ressource used to code those evolutions.


µC0What should one buy? An Amiga One or a Pegasus board??

µC2ah ah... An amigaOne. Definitively. Because of AmigaOS4. Now, look the products: they look the same but they are made by two differents teams. There is some kind of war between, which is fun because there is no money to gain behind that.

µC2Here in France it really got very violent, some people got completely schizophrenic about this affair. The fact is, µC7Genesi/Thendic µC2was in Paris around 2002, and lots of trolling was done to promote morphos around this date by people who was actually paid for doing it, and claim os4 will never exist because µC5Hyperion µC2is incompetent. At the times, all was about technical arguments, and legitimacy of being the new amigaOS. Currently, it is only and only a fight for the power (you know, there is Aros, too).

µC2On french Amiga website amigaimpact, you can read things like: "amigaOS4 is immoral" for a reason or another, because the morphos community just spend their times chatting between them and agreeing with each other a lot. Also, a lot of people claiming they "choosed morphos" actually got a free pegasos and choosed nothing. µC4Bill BuckµC2 is very rich, he offers pegasos to everyone asks. At the time, I actually bought one to support the morphos effort. But the money of the pegasos were never used for morphos.

µC2So... for the rest, see the D.Gerber page at http://www.morphos.net/ about what Bill Buck can do. Some people involved in the amigaOne also received some death menace by mail. Actually, when you buy a pegasos, all the money go to bplan and Bill Buck, and zero euros to the morphos team. When you buy an amigaOne, you will see on your bill that 100 euros are for OS4 and OS4 only. Actually, OS4 had 5 regulars which job is to code OS4, while it just became clear that morphos will never be sold as a product, because distributing money to developper would be impossible.

µC2Also, µC7Ralph SchmidtµC2, who is the mos kernel developper, claimed he doesn't care anymore of the pegasos version, because of disagreements with µC6Stephan StuntzµC2 (MUI), who left the team.
µC2But these stories are not really interesting. OS4 is. It really looks professional when you discover it for the first time. It is an OS3.9 evolution, and I mean, everything has evolved. There are details everywhere, a native special USB stack and TCP/IP integrated in the system.

µC2At the moment (May 2005) the only missing features are a 3d API and warpos emulation. But I'm in touch with some official betatesters: It already works and will feature in an update soon.



